5.4 Commercial Buyout Option
Where a Cooperation Result is initially owned by Party A alone or jointly owned, Party B may seek a negotiated buyout of Party A's relevant interest by delivering a written buyout request to Party A. The Parties shall negotiate in good faith for a period of thirty (30) calendar days following such request. Unless the Parties agree otherwise in writing, the following figures shall serve as non-binding reference pricing only and shall not constitute an offer or create any obligation to transact:
(a) one-time patent buyout fee: USD 36,000 per patent family;
(b) running royalty option: USD 1.80 per commercialized product unit;
(c) milestone payment: additional USD 18,000 upon cumulative sales exceeding 30,000 units within twenty-four (24) months after first commercial launch.
No transfer of Patent Rights shall occur unless and until the Parties execute a separate written assignment or license agreement in accordance with applicable law. These reference figures shall be subject to adjustment by mutual written agreement to reflect changes in the scope of the relevant patent family, market conditions, or other material factors.
